80.4	Herculaneum	Herculaneum	Herculaneum (in modern Italian Ercolano) was an ancient Roman town destroyed by volcanic pyroclastic flows in 79 C.E., located in the territory of the current commune of Ercolano, in the Italian region of Campania in the shadow of Mt. Vesuvius.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/010319_25_Ercolano_scavi_.JPG/250px-010319_25_Ercolano_scavi_.JPG
